{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The request sent to the external API always includes the complete list of valid taxonomy labels.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is module handoff (request builder -> API client). An in-process fake client that captures outbound payload can catch missing/partial taxonomy labels. Rejected System because behavior text is about request contents, not real network/OS/subprocess. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because correctness does not depend on model output quality or multi-step agent decisions.","test_description":"Wire classifier module to a fake API transport that records the sent request. Call classify() with a taxonomy, then assert the outbound payload contains the full label list exactly as configured.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When the API returns a label that is not in the taxonomy, the module returns \"unknown\" instead of forwarding the unexpected value to the caller.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is deterministic normalization/validation logic on returned label membership. The failure can be reproduced with direct function/object input, no real infra needed. Rejected Integration because behavior text focuses on mapping invalid label -> \"unknown\", not cross-module state propagation.","test_description":"Call the normalization/validation path with taxonomy [legal, technical, financial, other] and raw label \"medical\"; assert final output is \"unknown\".","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.7,"Integration":0.23,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"For identical raw API responses, the module's normalization step always produces the same final label.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Pure determinism/idempotence property of normalization for identical input. No module boundary, OS, network, or model-output-quality dependency is required. Rejected higher levels because behavior text explicitly constrains to identical raw responses and the normalization step.","test_description":"Run normalization repeatedly (or property-based) with the same raw response payload and taxonomy; assert every run returns the same label.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.88,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"On repeated live API calls for the same document and taxonomy, the returned label remains consistent unless the provider response itself changes.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires repeated live AI calls and consistency of provider/model decisions. A stub would hide real model variability. Rejected Workflow because this is repeated single-step classification calls, not a multi-stage agent pipeline with distinct agentic handoffs.","test_description":"Execute N live classification calls against the real provider for the same document+taxonomy, record raw provider outputs and final labels, and assert label changes only when provider response content changes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.82,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Request construction enforces the configured token budget before dispatch (for example truncate/reject according to policy).","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Budget enforcement at construction time is deterministic policy logic (count/check then truncate/reject). Can be validated without real API/network. Rejected Integration/System because behavior text says \"before dispatch\" and does not require observing external infra.","test_description":"Invoke request-construction with over-budget input and configured policy;